My whole 🌎 in a photo:

This session was in December. It was windy and cold. I had layers under the kids clothes. I had it in my mind I wanted Levi’s 6/7 mo photos at the beach like Gianna’s 😅 They were troopers… worth the freezing toes because these memories are now documented forever. The day after Levi’s 2nd tooth popped and now he has 6! So much changes so quickly with these babies it’s hard to grasp when you’re in the moment. My Husband gave me a hard time about taking these photos and said we didn’t need them, but deep down I couldn’t let it go… (first he knew what he married 😅📷) and second, my photos of my babies with ME in them are my greatest treasure. I am teary eyed writing this. 

Schedule the photoshoot mama. Don’t wait for that perfect moment, time waits for no one. If you’re like me, these photos are your only tangible memory of documenting how little they once were.💓

Photos by my dear friend @savanphotography

Levi Ryan, you are the missing piece to our little puzzle! You have the best giggle, the sweetest smile, and we are all obsessed with you! From that little curl on the top of your head, to playing chase with you, saying “ball, book, and buh bye”, your 7 little teeth, and your sweet demeanor you are an answered prayer! You turned 10 months on my birthday this year, and last year on my 31st birthday you were 31 weeks… what a difference a year can make! We love you handsome 💛

Happy 40th Birthday to my best friend 🥹 Ryan, you’re my rock. You are the best part of me. You’re the one who supports me in everything I do, who dreams with me, laughs with me, who made me a Mama, who has the most selfless caring heart… You deserve the best year yet, and I can’t wait to see how God uses this time in our lives as a testimony of His faithfulness and love. You amaze me with your strength, bravery, and BIG faith through it all. I love you forever and always, I’ll never stop loving you. 💛

Praying for a low grade curable tumor with a manageable treatment plan 🙏🏻 Complete healing!

Beyond grateful for everyone’s prayers, messages, and kind words this past week. As we wait for the diagnosis on my Hubby, we are doing our best to jump back into normal life and take these moments slow.

It’s wild to me that we need these reminders that life is so fragile, rather than treating each day as a gift. My “why” behind what I do has grown immensely and I’ll be sharing more on that soon.

This sweet family has given me the opportunity to capture S’s newborn session, 3 month, 7 month, 1 year coming in June, and their wedding later this year. Growing with a family is my absolute favorite thing and I’m eternally grateful for the Clients who let me document their lives biggest milestones.
